thread.title_full: 5X GRAMMY AWARD WINNER MALIK YUSEF RESURRECTS G.O.O.D. FRIDAYS WITH RELEASE OF HIS NEW MIXTAPE G.M.G.N. "THE LEAQUEL" UNHEARD & UNFINISHED JOINTS

author: prbuzz.com
title: 5X GRAMMY AWARD WINNER MALIK YUSEF RESURRECTS G.O.O.D. FRIDAYS WITH RELEASE OF HIS NEW MIXTAPE G.M.G.N. "THE LEAQUEL" UNHEARD & UNFINISHED JOINTS
text:
LOS ANGELES - In the spirit of Kanye West's infamous G.O.O.D. Friday series, 5x Grammy Award Winner Malik Yusef releases G.O.O.D. Morning G.O.O.D. Night The "Leaquel," Unheard & Unfinished Joints on Friday October 2nd, 2015. As the title implies, tracks on this project are comprised of leaked material from previous G.O.O.D. Music sessions, and unheard gems from prior releases like Common's "Nobody's Smiling," and "Sin City" from Cruel Summer.
What started out as just a studio album back in 2009 has now transformed into a full-fledged series. The third installment to the now trilogy follows up last year's summer release of G.M.G.N. Deconstructed, which saw features from Mr. West himself, Big Sean, KRS-One, Adam Levine, GLC, Common, John Legend, Twista & others. The release garnered over 7MM total impressions.
As reported earlier, features on the new mixtape come courtesy of G.O.O.D. Music's CyHi The Prynce on "We Ain't Playin'" & producer Travis Scott on "Sin City (Original)" - and others such as Raheem DeVaughn, Chip Tha Ripper, JV, Grande Marshall, Young Savage, Ab-Liva, Black, Kentrell, and YouTube sensations Andrew Garcia, Jay Hayden, The Johnsoton Brothers, Brandon Skeie, J. Rice, Casey Cooper, and new comer Megan Elizabeth. Production duties handled this time around come predominately from Nate "Impact" Jolley &D.Cross, as well as Tommy Brown, Big Duke, Rami, Brian K. Bolton, Kevin M. Cairns, Hit Fluid Blue, KC, Mind Killa, Mizzy Beats, and The 11th Hour.
In collaboration with Babe Method & Clynton Blacklaws, The Pretty Gurl Gang inclusive of Playboy playmates Abby Parece, CJ Sparxx, Pashence Marie, Holly Wolf, Chrystiane Gaygher, Amber Quinn, and Eric Gea can be heard featured throughout the exclusive Coast2Coast mixtape, and joined the Chi-Town legend directly in-studio during the creation process for an official Babe Method Experience. Even celebrity make-up artists & hair stylists Jeton Mullaliu & Danyel Nicole joined in on the fun and making of this sure to be club favorite.
Making major moves all while saving the planet, Yusef sat with Pope Francis on his nationwide Act On Climate Tour stop in Washington D.C. before dropping the projects first single, "Amazing" featuring JV from Yusef’s The Private Plane collection. His focused efforts in the green space continue to open up partnerships & collaborations with major world leaders, influencers, and tastemakers in every market. His music continues to be a light for social justice issues, taking him around the world and in the homes & hearts of all the huddled masses while maintaining the integrity of his art.

About Malik Yusef
Wordsmyth, writer, super producer, poet, philanthropist, film maker, and fashionista – The Chicago Legend and 5x Grammy Award Winner is most notably recognized for his collaborative efforts with creative genius, and superstar friend Kanye West, but also for his extensive work in the community & intellectual creativity. Yusef is a key influencer in the community. He seeks to use his star power and influence to help prevent others from making the same mistakes he did in his youth. His initiatives like People's Climate Music & Act on Climate make him an invaluable icon and tastemaker in today’s global industry. Learn more at http://malikyusefjones.com .
